      "title" : "The day you let k-pop soundtrack every hour from sunrise to sunset",
      "description" : "Early morning drifted through Kali Uchis and Tate McRae, but by mid-morning, k-pop took the reins—BTS, BLACKPINK, NCT 127, and more, with “Hero (Prod. by Primary)” looping across sessions. 293 minutes, 94 tracks, 60 artists—your most k-pop–packed day of the year, outpacing even your annual top genre stats.",
